  <summary date="2020-06-25T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Removing Confederate Names and Symbols from Our Military Act of 2020

This bill requires the Department of Defense (DOD) to remove from its property, and prohibits DOD from using or displaying in the future, any name, symbol, display, monument, or paraphernalia that honors or commemorates the Confederacy or anyone who served voluntarily with the Confederacy. The removal requirement does not apply to grave markers.</summary>
